\begin_layout Section
Introduction 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Qur'an is the sacred book of Muslims, it is the basis of several sciences,
 such as Tafssir, translation, recitation, etc.
 The information contained in the Qur'anic text are the sources of these
 sciences, hence the need for a powerful search system that offers lots
 of features specific to the Qur'an.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Our subject is to achieve such a system, so in this chapter, we will first
 clarify the definition of the Qur'an, then we will see in brief the main
 steps of the evolution of the Qur'an through time and how it was written,
 edited and computerized, then we will study the mus'haf and sciences of
 the Qur'an.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then we will see the benefits and challenges of computerization of the Qur'an,
 in particular, the script Uthmani, verification and authentication of Mus'haf.
\end_layout

